<recipe>
<title>
Frosted Caramel Apple Cookies
</title>
<details>
SERVINGS: 24
</details>
<ingredients>
COOKIES
1/2 c . butter softened, divided
3/4 c . granulated sugar
1/4 c . brown sugar packed
1 large egg
1 tsp . vanilla extract
1/2 c . apple cider
2 1/2 c . all-purpose flour
1 tsp . baking soda
1 tsp . apple pie spice
1/4 tsp . salt
1 c . peeled shredded tart apple (like a Granny Smith)
1/2 c . chopped pecans
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 375 F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together 1/3 cup butter and sugars until very well-combined.
Beat in egg and vanilla until well-combined.
Add apple cider, and beat in.
Stir in flour, baking soda, apple pie spice, and salt until just combined.
Drop 1.5 tablespoons (medium cookie scoop) of dough onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake for about 9-12 minutes, or until the edges are lightly browned.
Let cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes, and then remove to wire cooling rack to finish cooling.
To make the frosting, stir together remaining butter, brown sugar, and apple cider in a saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Frost cooled cookies, and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
</instructions>
</recipe>
